returns._authorized: Whether the account is authorized or not

exit(address,uint256).details: This function destroys the collateral representation from inside the system      and exits the collateral from this adapter. The transferred collateral uses      the same decimals as the original collateral token.

params._account: Account to which we transfer the collateral out of the system
params._wei: Amount of collateral to transfer to account (represented as a number with token decimals)

join(address,uint256).details: This function locks collateral in the adapter and creates a representation of      the locked collateral inside the system. The representation uses 18 decimals.

params._account: Account to which we add collateral into the system
params._wei: Amount of collateral to transfer in the system (represented as a number with token decimals)

authorizedAccounts(address).notice: Checks whether an account is authorized

collateralType().notice: System name of the collateral type

multiplier().notice: Multiplier used to transform collateral into 18 decimals within the system
